81.7	Anna_Hazare	Anna Hazare	Kisan Baburao Hazare ·) (born 15 June 1937), popularly known as Anna Hazare ·) (Marathi: , ) is an Indian social activist and a prominent leader in the 2011 Indian anti-corruption movement, using nonviolent methods following the teachings of Mahatma Gandhi. Hazare also contributed to the development and structuring of Ralegan Siddhi, a village in Parner taluka of Ahmednagar district, Maharashtra, India. He was awarded the Padma Bhushan—the third-highest civilian award—by the Government of India in 1992 for his efforts in establishing this village as a model for others.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/57/Anna_Hazare.jpg/220px-Anna_Hazare.jpg
